          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-235",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.9372
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Five fission foils, each",
                "containing 7.855x10**-3 microg of 93.72 percent U235,",
                "were prepared by the standard method. Two additional",
                "foils were prepared by slight variations of this",
                "method: one, without final ignition, to test whether",
                "ignition affects the escape of fission recoils; and the",
                " other, by stippling the foil solution and rinse in",
                "small droplets over the surface of the Pt before",
                "evaporation and ignition, to test whether possible",
                "clumping of the U was great enough to cause loss of",
                "fission recoils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC",
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gas counters were of glass, 2 cm in",
                "diameter and 30 cm long, with chemically deposited",
                "silver cathodes whose volumes had been measured to",
                "within 0.2 percent."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "INTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two slug solutions were prepared",
                "independently of each other by diluting aliquots of",
                "the U235 stock solution. The slug was bombarded in",
                "the space between the two fission foils for an hour.",
                "The total of the recorded fissions of each foil was",
                "then corrected for background and counting-rate loss,",
                "divided by 60 to give the foil fission rate as",
                "fissions per min, and multiplied by the ratio of",
                "slug weight to foil weight to give the slug fission",
                "rate."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Surprisingly, modern T1/2 values for 133Xe and 135Xe",
                "are 5.2475 d and 9.14 H, respectively. Almost no",
                "changes in the last 65 years."
              ]
            }
          ],
